time complexity: O(target log target)
space complexity: O(target)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Dynamic programming is used to store the minimum number of instructions required to reach each position up to the target, optimizing the search by avoiding redundant calculations and leveraging the properties of the 'A' and 'R' instructions to minimize the number of operations.
